caption.text: Mom sent this photo to me today, and said it was my first on-stage experience. I couldn't remember which song was played. But I remember it was for celebrating the National Children's Day.  I guess I was the first elementary student who leaned some music instruments in that village where I live for 12 years. The village was really a small village with only 1 school, 1 farmer market, and a few population. It's a village where everyone knows each other, where sometimes has no electricity and water supplies for couple days. Every Saturday, I took tricycle--bus--and tricycle again, total 2 hours journey to get into the town to learn violin. I can see my little village disappeared in the rear window, and the trees, houses, unknown people oncoming to you ... That "2 hours" that spent on the road has become the most happiest time in my life. I had imaging myself as an explorer, a dreamer, or a soldier step on his adventure without fear...
